		<ns0:id>http://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/full/2775</ns0:id><ns0:author>
			<ns0:name>robertm@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/robertm@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Being able to look at the phdrs from withing a program will simplify
the handling of tls and ehframes and make it resemble
the standard toolchains.
 
In the ehframe case, this will likely break some odd dependencies
of libgcc_eh on libc.
In the tls case, we can get rid of some custom linkerdefs.

Supporting phdr might require some slight changes to sel_ldr.
It is important to get those in early, so that they make into chrome.

On the linker side the necessary changes are in the process of being
upstreamed to gold by mcgrathr.

Once the pnacl toolchain supports this feature, enabling it for nacl-gcc
shouldn't be difficult.
